SIMPLE: wader
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wader
<hw>Wad"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or
that which, wades.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any long-legged bird that wades
in the water in search of food, especially any species of limicoline or
grallatorial birds; -- called also <altname>wading bird</altname>. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> <it>g</it>, under <er>Aves</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wading</ent>⟦br⟧
